        {
          "type": "thinking",
          "thinking": "Now I need to look for split reimbursement patterns. According to rule 第十一条 (Article 11) of the expense reimbursement policy:\n- Same employee, same expense type, within 7 days, 2+ reimbursements\n- Combined amount reaching the \"较高审批线\" (higher approval threshold) from Authorization Management 附件二\n\nLet me think about what \"较高审批线\" means. Looking at the approval levels:\n- AR-01: 0~3000 → 部门经理\n- AR-02: 3000~10000 → 部门经理+财务复核\n- AR-03: 10000~50000 → 部门总经理\n- AR-04: 50000~200000 → 分管副总\n- AR-05: ≥200000 → 总经理办公会\n\nThe \"较高审批线\" likely means the next level up. If individual expenses are at AR-01 level (under 3000), but combined they go to AR-02 (3000-10000), that would be a concern.\n\nLet me search for potential split reimbursements. I'll look for same employee, same expense type, within 7 days.\n\nLet me search for specific patterns. Let me look at employees with business_entertainment expenses first, as that's a common area for splitting.",
          "signature": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Let me look for potential split reimbursement patterns by checking employees who filed similar expense types close together."
        },
